jobs_results.title: Mobile App Developer (Capacitor, iOS, Android)
jobs_results.description:
Natural Cycles is a leading women’s health company that developed the world’s first birth control app, used by millions globally. We are a fast growing startup, and we promote an international working environment filled with smart and ambitious colleagues based in Stockholm, Geneva, New York, and remotely. Our mission is to pioneer women’s health through research and passion, empowering every woman with the knowledge she needs to take charge of her health.

You’re a Mobile App Developer who thrives in a fast-paced, data-driven, analytical and agile environment. Your soft skills shine and you can communicate with ease in English. You are passionate about technology, team work, but also have a responsibility and autonomy in your work. You are able to work efficiently in a remote work environment, in a setting where online and asynchronous communication is the foundation. You will be joining the Product team and working on the integration of the app with external temperature measuring devices.

What you will be doing
• Ship top-quality, performant, accessible, inclusive user interfaces, features and products
• Work on the device integrations with the Natural Cycles core App (built as a Hybrid Web application, packaged for iOS and Android)
• Work in an agile team together with other software engineers, product manager, designers & testers
• Work in close collaboration with stakeholders across the organization to deliver top-quality user interfaces and features
• Work hands-on with data insights and analytics and if possible, always take the data driven approach
• Ensure continuous delivery of new releases while working in an agile way
• Maintain a healthy codebase

What skills and experience we think you have
• Experience in mobile app development: building and maintaining iOS and Android applications
• Experience in frontend web/app development: building websites, web applications, responsive layout
• Experience with Swift and Kotlin
• Experience with TypeScript and frontend Javascript frameworks such as Angular, React, or Vue
• Good understanding of modern CSS (e.g Flexbox, Grid), experience with modern pre/post-processors, such as SASS, PostCSS
• Experience working with git, github, pull requests, code review, etc.

Not required but it would be a bonus if you also have:
• Experience with building software that integrates with connected devices (via Bluetooth, API etc)
• Experience with Node.js backend development
• A passion for women’s health

Our technology stack includes:
• TypeScript, Node.js, Express.js running on GCP AppEngine
• Swift, Kotlin in our mobile apps
• Ionic, Angular, Capacitor, React, Gatsby on the Frontend
• Firebase Hosting
• Highly automated CI pipelines (Github Actions)
• AppStore/GooglePlay releases on a biweekly basis
• We <3 Open Source, encourage Open Source contributions and often open our general-purpose repositories

What we offer
• Flexible work arrangement – you will be part of a team based in and around Stockholm that values effective collaboration and transparent communication, irrespective of work location
• Professional development – you will collaborate with industry leading developers, promoting continuous growth and skill enhancement
• Modern technology – you will leverage innovative technologies and tools, within an environment that empowers you to contribute ideas and take ownership of your work
• Impactful projects – you will contribute to groundbreaking projects that redefine industry standards and create tangible value
• Commitment to quality – you will join a dynamic and progressive organization that prioritizes profitable, long-term product development

Location

We are remote-friendly, but we find great value in being able to connect with our teams in person. Most of the product development team you will work with is located in Stockholm.Not living in Sweden? No problem! We offer relocation support to help you move.

Sounds interesting?

If you want to be part of a successful team, we encourage you to apply for this position as soon as possible.

We look forward to hearing from you!

Note: We are not looking for consultants or help from recruitment agencies

How to apply

To apply, just upload your CV and answer the questions on the application form. Keep in mind that we can’t accept applications through email because of GDPR, and only applications submitted via the career site (and in English) will be considered.

At Natural Cycles we value diversity and inclusion because we know that teams with people from different backgrounds and experiences are stronger. We welcome candidates from all walks of life and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees and candidates.

jobs_results.title: iOS Developer till Tunstall
jobs_results.description:
Tunstall är världsledande inom innovativ välfärdsteknologi; vi utvecklar tekniska lösningar och system för vård och omsorg.Vi drivs av att hjälpa individer som befinner sig i en utsatt situation och vår vision är att forma en värld där människor har friheten att leva ett fullvärdigt liv på den plats dom själva valt.

Vill du också arbeta i ett affärsdrivet och marknadsledande bolag? Gärna ett som har tydligt syfte och goda värdegrunder?

Då kanske rollen som iOS Developer är något för dig!

Om rollen

På vårt nordiska huvudkontor i Malmö är vi ca 50 personer inom R&D.

Som iOS Developer blir du en del av ett välfungerande och kompetent team som arbetar med att vidareutveckla och förbättra våra appar.

Våra appar används av personal inom äldreomsorgen, bland annat för att planera vårdbesök och för att hantera och agera på larm från brukare. Med andra ord är dina insatser direkt kopplade till en bättre vardag för många människor!

Som iOS Developer kommer du att:
• Utveckla och underhålla iOS-appar med hög teknisk kvalitet.
• Samarbeta med UX-designers och testare för att skapa användarvänliga lösningar.
• Arbeta nära produktavdelningen för att omsätta kundkrav och behov till funktionella och innovativa applikationer.
• Utforska och implementera nya tekniker och arbetssätt.

Vi jobbar enligt det agila ramverket SAFe.

Om dig

Vi söker dig som har gedigen erfarenhet av modern iOS-, Swift & Swift UI-utveckling. Du är tekniskt nyfiken och har ett starkt driv att hitta nya lösningar.

För att lyckas i rollen tror vi att du:
• Har erfarenhet av att utveckla användarvänliga appar
• Motiveras av att arbeta i ett team med stark sammanhållning och gemensamt mål.

Du behärskar god svenska och engelska, både i tal och skrift.

Hos Tunstall får du möjlighet att arbeta i en trygg och stabil organisation med stor framtidstro. Vi är stolta över att ligga i framkant för att utveckla framtidens tekniska lösningar för en bättre vård.

Vår arbetsmiljö som präglas av hjälpsamhet och samarbete.

Placering och ansökan

Tjänsten är placerad i Malmö med möjlighet till hybridarbete.

I denna rekrytering samarbetar vi med Cabeza AB. För frågor om rollen, kontakta rekryteringskonsult Malin Schultz: malin.schultz@cabeza.se

Vill du vara med och göra skillnad? Skicka in din ansökan redan idag! Vi ser fram emot att lära känna dig.

jobs_results.title: iOS Developer till Sportswik
jobs_results.description:
Vill du kombinera din passion för teknik och sport? Sportswik söker en engagerad iOS-utvecklare som vill vara en del av ett innovativt team och bidra till framtidens sportbevakning!

Om oss

Sportswik revolutionerar mediabevakningen av idrott genom att ge varje match samma bevakning som proffsidrott. Vår app gör det möjligt för alla, från supportrar till lagledare, att rapportera live via bilder, video, kommentarer och resultat. Vi samarbetar med stora idrottsförbund som Svenska Fotbollförbundet och Innebandyförbundet för att skapa användargenererat innehåll för tusentals matcher.

Vi är ett passionerat startup-bolag med stora ambitioner, och söker nu ytterligare iOS utvecklare som vill hjälpa oss fortsätta expandera och utveckla vår plattform.

Om rollen

Som iOS-utvecklare hos Sportswik kommer du att vara en viktig del av vårt team och arbeta med den senaste tekniken för att skapa framtidens mediaplattform för sport. Du får möjligheten att arbeta med hela utvecklingscykeln från design till implementering och underhåll av vår iOS-app, och vara med och utveckla nya funktioner som förbättrar användarupplevelsen för sportfans världen över.

Vem är du?

Vi söker dig som har ett genuint intresse för både teknik och sport, och som älskar att skapa smarta och användarvänliga lösningar. Du trivs i en startup-miljö där tempot är högt, innovation är i fokus och dina idéer kan förverkligas snabbt. Vi ser gärna att du har en akademisk utbildning med några års erfarenhet av iOS utveckling. Du är bekant med Objective-C, Swift och iOS-ramverk, RESTful API samt god problemlösningsförmåga. Har du erfarenhet som full-stack utvecklare ser vi det som meriterande, men inte ett krav.

Hos oss handlar det om laget, före jaget. Där vi tillsammans tar ett ansvar för att säkerställa att vi fortsätter leverera en produkt i världsklass och konstant utmanar varandra för att bli bättre.

Varför Sportswik?

Hos oss får du en unik möjlighet att vara med och utveckla framtidens mediaplattform för sport. Du blir en del av ett dynamiskt och ambitiöst team i Umeå som ligger i teknikens framkant. Vi erbjuder en kreativ arbetsmiljö med stor möjlighet att påverka ditt arbete och företagets utveckling.

Vad vi erbjuder:
• En öppen och inspirerande arbetsmiljö där innovation står i centrum.
• Flexibla arbetstider och möjlighet att påverka
• Chansen att arbeta med en produkt som dagligen engagerar tusentals användare.
• Bra lön och bra förmåner
• Möjlighet att arbeta med sport och mot idrottsförbund

Ansökan

I denna rekrytering har vi valt att samarbeta med Talentify. Alla frågor gällande processen eller tjänsten hänvisas till Hanna Grahn, hanna@talentify.se

jobs_results.title: Senior iOS Engineer
jobs_results.description:
Join us in creating world-class creativity apps used by millions of people.

Appostrophe is a mobile app development company creating easy-to-use design tools that unlock people's creativity. Our portfolio consists of top-listed apps such as SCRL, Text Art, and Add Text that are used and loved by millions of people worldwide. We’re a small, ambitious team that enjoys working together in central Stockholm and are looking for more like-minded people to join our mission.

We are looking for a talented Senior iOS Engineer to help build, maintain, and optimize advanced creativity apps as an integral part of a dynamic product development team.

What you will do
• Create high-quality and robust features, owning the development process from planning to final delivery.
• Work closely with product managers, designers, and other engineers to plan and ensure high-quality results.
• Work with the engineering team to ensure best practices and code standards are followed.
• Leverage usage data and experimentation results to evaluate the performance and impact of released features, troubleshoot potential issues, and ideate new hypotheses for further iterations.
• Create and improve cross-app libraries to improve our productivity and workflow.
• Stay up-to-date with the latest developments in the iOS ecosystem (developer tools, new iOS APIs).
• Take an active role in roadmap planning, code reviews, problem solving, and testing sessions.

You should have
• Extensive experience in iOS development and Swift.
• Experience working on consumer apps with large user bases.
• A proven track record of delivering excellent and reliable code.
• A talent for technical problem solving and designing effective and maintainable abstractions.
• An ability to communicate concepts and solutions clearly and effectively to internal stakeholders.
• An ability to work at a high pace without compromising quality.
• A can-do attitude. Be a self-motivated problem solver with an eye for details and an internal drive for excellence.

We offer
• Opportunity to be creative and test new ideas.
• Important role in a successful startup.
• Great colleagues and office in central Stockholm.
• Competitive salary.

jobs_results.title: Senior Software Developer - iOS
jobs_results.description:
We are currently looking for a Senior/Lead Developer to join our team and help us deliver quality software solutions that are fit for use and purpose. This role is hybrid and will be based from our Malmo (Sweden) office .

But there’s more to this than just the ‘day job’. Tunstall is embarking upon a significant technical and business transformation programme that is focusing on changing the way in which we host and deliver our market leading solutions.

A bit about us:

Tunstall is a market-leading health and care technology provider .

We’re passionate about ensuring our team reflects the brilliant and unique qualities of the people and communities we support. Our incredible team of more than 3,000 colleagues provides life saving and life changing technology and services to millions of people in 18 different countries .

At Tunstall you’ll find a place where you’re valued and celebrated for being yourself. We empower our people to deliver the very best teamwork, innovation and thought leadership by creating an environment where we champion diversity and inclusion. We demonstrate our commitment to diversity and inclusion at each step. From our open, fair, and transparent recruitment processes, through to the many development and career growth opportunities we provide.

Each Tunstall colleague has a superpower… they’re unique. No one else is them, and we think that’s special. Come and join our mission and be part of our team, our One Tunstall team.

What will you be doing in this role?

As a Senior Developer at Tunstall, you will be responsible for continuously researching and integrating new technologies and best practices to enhance the development process and improve application performance.

Main tasks for this role include:
• Maintain and develop iOS mobile apps
• Participate in knowledge-sharing sessions to promote new ideas and innovation
• Continuously discover, evaluate, and implement new technologies to maximize development efficiency

The Ideal candidate:

Any experience of working within a business moving from Legacy to modern systems and working with cloud micro services using Microsoft and / or mobile applications would be desirable, but not essential.

Required skills and experience
• Experience working with Swift, Swift UI and Swift package manager.
• BLE communication protocol and the relevant iOS APIs
• Experience with RESTful APIs and integration with cloud services
• Experience of programming Swift for iOS applications
• Proficient in English and Swedish (business level)

Required competencies
• Senior level competency with iOS including Swift.

If you are not sure if you have the relevant skills or experience, then please apply (only takes a few minutes) and let our team review and come back to you.

What we offer:
• Collective agreement
• Service pension
• Health care allowance
• Hybrid working
• A warm and welcoming team environment
• Development and the chance to build a rewarding career
• Modern office in Hyllie, Malmö
• Exciting products and services in a growing industry

jobs_results.title: Mobile Developer
jobs_results.description:
This a Full Remote job, the offer is available from: Sweden

At Coody, we're revolutionizing consulting by combining the freedom and flexibility of freelancing with the security of traditional employment. With us, you'll receive a maxed out salary with a full benefit package, the opportunity to work remotely and assignments that are both fun and challenging.

On average, joining Coody means increasing your salary by 44%. How do we do it?

The math is simple. We pay you more by cutting unnecessary costs — no overpaid bosses, no luxurious conferences, and no fancy offices. Instead, we invest in what matters: you.

Coody is all about giving you as an individual the chance to have a free and flexible life to live for your own priorities. Welcome to Gravity Free Consulting.

Gravity Free Consulting @ Coody Means:
• Maximized Compensation: Typically a 44% salary increase.
• Safety & Comfort: Employment with a generous benefits package.
• Freedom & Flexibility: No bosses. All digital. Fully remote for those who prefer.
• Shaping the Future: Assignments with industry innovators like Topgolf, Spotify, Tobii, Volumental, Paradox, Volvo Cars, Varjo, and exciting startups and scale-ups.

ABOUT US

Coody is a growing and dynamic group of people who are the tech stars of the future. We consists of about 13 different nationalities and work on assignments for digital game changers across Sweden, Finland, USA and the UK, in industries such as EV, Gaming, AI, MedTech, AR and FinTech.

We’re more than a company — we’re a community platform. Our approach is built on trust and autonomy. We keep corporate bullshit to a minimum and focus on what benefits our consultants most. Explore our employee handbook for more insight into a genuine supportive, consultant-first environment.

WHAT YOU'LL BE DOING

As a Mobile Developer consultant, you'll tackle technically challenging and engaging assignments that empower companies to enhance their teams and projects. You will craft high-quality, efficient, and maintainable code using Android or iOS technologies (or both). Collaborating closely with cross-functional teams, you'll play a vital role in defining, designing, and delivering new features.

You'll need to be adaptable and ready to hit the ground running in new environments. We see new challenges and situations as opportunities for growth. Typically, you'll work on 1-2 different assignments per year for companies in a sector you're passionate about.

WHAT WE ARE LOOKING FOR
• 5+ years of experience working as an Mobile Developer
• Deep understanding of one or more technical areas stated below
• Fluency in English (verbal and written)
• Experience working in an agile environment
• A doers mindset with a proven track record of getting things done

WE WOULD LIKE TO SEE THAT YOU HAVE

Experience working with Kotlin, Swift, Flutter or React Native

Technical expertise from working with mobile related tools and frameworks for user critical applications

Unit testing experience and a solid understanding of the release cycle and familiarity with CI/CD pipelines

A degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Information technology, or a related field

We are looking for both Android and iOS developers so you do not necessarily need to match at all points to be eligible.

If Gravity Free Consulting at Coody aligns with your goals, and you bring the skills we're seeking, we’d love to hear from you. Apply today, and we’ll get back to you within a week if your profile fits our needs.

This offer from "Coody.io" has been enriched by Jobgether.com and got a 72% flex score.
